{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_19","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n \\\"test_generation_failed|human intervention|Human intervention|no test file|metadata_file|test_file|generated_loc|artifacts|failed to|failure reason|finalize|preserv|untracked|git status|did not compile or run tests|not compile or run tests|Per instruction\\\" ../2445-7f6c22dc -g '\"'!**/.git/**'\"'\"","aggregated_output":"../2445-7f6c22dc/LICENSE:84:shall be preserved to the maximum extent permitted taking into account\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/contributing/questions.json:5:    \"help\": \"Maven coordinates consist of three parts in the following format \\\"groupId:artifactId:version\\\". For more information visit: https://maven.apache.org/repositories/artifacts.html\"\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/contributing/questions.json:30:    \"help\": \"Enter the additional dependencies (press enter after each dependency) you want to include use in tests. Provide dependencies in form of Maven coordinates. Maven coordinates consist of three parts in the following format \\\"groupId:artifactId:version\\\". For more information visit: https://maven.apache.org/repositories/artifacts.html When you finish adding dependencies, type \\\"-\\\" to terminate the inclusion process.\"\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/README.md:42:It finds the issue linked by the PR, removes the issue assignee, rolls the linked project item from `In Progress` back to `Todo`, and preserves `Done` when another PR has already completed the issue.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair test sources or test dependencies after an existing library is bumped and the new version no longer compiles with the old test code. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to preserve working coverage across the version update rather than prove a brand-new metadata contribution from scratch.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:87:- The fix makes compilation pass by weakening or bypassing the test instead of adapting it to the changed API while preserving meaningful coverage.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:20:import org.gradle.api.artifacts.Configuration;\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:21:import org.gradle.api.artifacts.dsl.DependencyHandler;\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtils.java:15: * Utility methods for creating native-image options that track and preserve dynamic access\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/TestedVersionUpdaterTask.java:266:                // Keep the old directory when other stats artifacts still exist in it.\n../2445-7f6c22dc/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsSchemaValidator.java:352:                    throw new GradleException(\"Failed to list metadata artifacts under \" + groupDir, e);\n../2445-7f6c22dc/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:30:Two properties make this achievable: the reachability-metadata schema is itself additive (every entry is gated on `typeReachable`, FR-M-2), and `native-image` defaults to runtime initialization when no build-time directives are supplied. The hard constraints below preserve that additivity — they are not editorial scope choices 